{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 19:43:04.816393", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope and Topology\n- SDN spine–leaf with OVS switches: leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1\n- Hosts on 10.0.0.0/24: host_1_1, host_1_2 (on leaf_1), host_2_1, host_2_2 (on leaf_2)\n- Management network 20.0.0.0/24; controller at 20.0.0.100; switches managed via OpenFlow\n\n1) Health and Anomaly Detection\n- End-to-end and intra-leaf connectivity failure:\n  - host_1_1 → host_1_2: 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable”\n  - host_1_1 → host_2_1: 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable”\n  - host_2_1 → host_2_2: 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable”\n- This indicates ARP resolution is failing and L2 forwarding is not occurring, even between hosts on the same leaf switch.\n\n2) Localization of Faulty Components\n- Hosts:\n  - Interfaces up with correct IPs (10.0.0.x/24) and link-local routes. No apparent host misconfiguration.\n- OVS switches (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1):\n  - All three are configured with a controller at tcp:20.0.0.100:6633 and fail_mode: secure.\n  - No OpenFlow rules installed on any switch (ovs-ofctl -O OpenFlow13 dump-flows returns empty).\n  - Controller connectivity state on all bridges shows not connected:\n    - ovs-vsctl get Controller <bridge> is_connected → false\n    - ovs-vsctl get Controller <bridge> connection_state → false\n  - OpenFlow port statistics:\n    - leaf_1 and leaf_2 show RX packets on host-facing ports (eth0/eth1) but zero TX on all ports, consistent with frames being dropped (no forwarding).\n    - spine_1 shows zero traffic, consistent with no inter-switch forwarding occurring.\n- Management network path:\n  - All switches can ping the controller IP 20.0.0.100 successfully (low-latency ICMP), indicating basic IP reachability to the controller host is fine.\n- Service state:\n  - systemctl reports openvswitch-switch “inactive (dead)” on all switches, yet OVS commands return valid info and bridges exist with ovs_version \"3.1.0\". This suggests OVS is running outside systemd or service state reporting is not indicative here; not the immediate cause of traffic drop.\n\n3) Root Cause Analysis\n- The SDN control-plane session between all OVS bridges (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) and the controller at 20.0.0.100:6633 is down (is_connected=false on all).\n- With fail_mode: secure and no OpenFlow rules installed, the switches do not perform any forwarding (including ARP floods), causing complete L2 isolation:\n  - Evidenced by:\n    - Empty flow tables on all switches.\n    - Host-facing ports receiving packets but transmitting none.\n    - Intra-leaf host-to-host pings failing with “Destination Host Unreachable.”\n- Since the switches can ping the controller IP, the control-plane failure is not IP reachability but likely one of:\n  - Controller application not listening/accepting on TCP port 6633.\n  - OpenFlow port mismatch (switches configured for 6633 while controller may use a different port, e.g., 6653).\n  - Controller process down or otherwise not establishing OpenFlow sessions.\n\nKey Findings Summary\n- Anomaly: Network-wide loss of host connectivity (including same-leaf communication).\n- Fault localization: All OVS switches’ OpenFlow control-plane to the controller is down; data-plane forwarding disabled due to fail_mode secure and no flows.\n- Root cause: Controller session failure (controller not connected/not programming flows), despite management IP reachability.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 19318, "output_tokens": 2713, "total_tokens": 22031, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 17664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 1856}}}
